  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/f8c5a5fe1223746692cfb9fc536cd93849e6feb1" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:6.553ex; height:2.509ex;" alt="{\displaystyle a\perp b\ ,}"></span> and in <a href="/wiki/Projective_geometry" title="Projective geometry">projective geometry</a> two points <i>b</i> and <i>c</i> are in <a href="/wiki/Perspective_(geometry)" title="Perspective (geometry)">perspective</a> when <span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle b\ \doublebarwedge \ c}">
